The paper deals with image attribute editing using generative networks, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a new architecture for learning the inverse function of the generator in an unsupervised setting, which involves the use of cost minimization techniques (cs.LG). They also mention the use of encoder networks for this purpose, which is a common technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves the manipulation of images, which is a topic related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
